        about: 'A prototype is just a hypothesis. Usability testing is how you find out if your hypothesis is right. Most first prototypes are wrong in at least one important way — the designers who build successful products are the ones who find out early and fix it before development. The 5-user rule is real: five users reveal 85% of usability problems. The remaining budget is better spent fixing the found problems and testing again.\n\nDeveloper handoff is where design decisions get lost if they are not documented. Dev Mode in Figma automates much of the annotation, but interaction notes, token names, and edge cases still require a designer\'s attention. Your case study is the final output — not just a gallery of screens, but evidence of your design thinking.',
